# STRATEGICLAND — Typography System

> Typography is **the building**. Color, motion, image are tenants.
> If the typography fails, the page fails — no amount of motion will rescue it.

---

## 1. Type Philosophy

- Type is **architecture**, not decoration.
- Default state of any text is **silent and confident**. Bold weights are reserved.
- Oversized type is the project's **primary visual instrument** — used as image, not as label.
- Never use type as UI chrome (no all-caps button labels, no decorative quote marks, no faux-pull-quotes).

---

## 2. Typeface System

The project uses **two typefaces only**. No third weight, no display alternates beyond what's listed.

### Primary Serif — Editorial Voice
- **Role:** display headlines, oversized chapter titles, pull quotes, image captions.
- **Recommended families** (any one, not multiple):
  - GT Sectra (preferred — paid)
  - Pangram Sans Rounded (alt)
  - **Free fallback:** *Fraunces* (variable, OFL) or *Newsreader* (variable, OFL).
- **Loaded via:** `next/font/local` (preferred) or `next/font/google` for free fallbacks.
- **Subset:** `latin`, `latin-ext` only.
- **Weights shipped:** 300 (Light), 400 (Regular), 500 (Medium). **Never** ship 700+.
- **Variable axis:** if available, use `opsz` (optical size) bound to font-size.

### Secondary Sans — Body & Functional
- **Role:** body copy, navigation, metadata, labels, captions ≤ 13px.
- **Recommended families:**
  - Söhne (preferred — paid)
  - **Free fallback:** *Inter* (variable, OFL) or *Geist Sans* (variable, OFL).
- **Weights shipped:** 400 (Regular), 500 (Medium). Nothing else.

### Mono (rare)
- Allowed only for editorial metadata (chapter numbers, frame counts, timecodes).
- **Free fallback:** *JetBrains Mono* (variable, OFL) or *Geist Mono*.
- Used **at most 1× per chapter**.

### Forbidden
- ❌ More than 2 typefaces simultaneously visible (mono counted separately and rare).
- ❌ Italics in sans-serif body. Italics allowed only in serif, sparingly, for emphasis or titles of works.
- ❌ Faux-bold, faux-italic.
- ❌ Web-safe fallbacks visible at any point — preload critical weights (`preload: true` on `next/font`).
- ❌ Any "modern geometric" sans (Poppins, Montserrat, Quicksand, etc.). They read as 2018 SaaS.

---

## 3. Type Scale

Modular, **not** ratio-locked. Designed for cinematic emphasis, not algorithmic uniformity.

| Token            | Desktop (≥1024) | Tablet (768–1023) | Mobile (≤767) | Use                                     |
|------------------|---------------:|-----------------:|--------------:|------------------------------------------|
| `type.epic`      | clamp(120px, 14vw, 240px) | 96px            | 72px          | Hero / chapter establishing title        |
| `type.display`   | clamp(72px, 8vw, 120px)   | 64px            | 48px          | Section openings, major headings         |
| `type.headline`  | 48px            | 40px             | 32px          | Sub-section / case study titles          |
| `type.title`     | 32px            | 28px             | 24px          | Minor titles, named lists                |
| `type.lede`      | 22px            | 20px             | 18px          | Opening paragraph, intro copy            |
| `type.body`      | 17px            | 17px             | 16px          | Default body                             |
| `type.caption`   | 13px            | 13px             | 12px          | Captions, metadata, timecodes            |
| `type.micro`     | 11px            | 11px             | 10px          | Eyebrows, frame numbers, fine print      |

```ts
export const TYPE_SCALE = {
  epic:     "clamp(72px, 14vw, 240px)",
  display:  "clamp(48px, 8vw, 120px)",
  headline: "clamp(32px, 4vw, 48px)",
  title:    "clamp(24px, 2.4vw, 32px)",
  lede:     "clamp(18px, 1.6vw, 22px)",
  body:     "17px",
  caption:  "13px",
  micro:    "11px",
} as const;
```

### Constraints
- Never invent intermediate sizes. Snap to the scale.
- Maximum **3 sizes per viewport** (see `cinematic-language.mdc`).
- `type.epic` may break the layout grid — it's expected. Always verify it doesn't break with the longest expected string.

---

## 4. Tracking (Letter-Spacing)

Tracking is inverse to size. Locked by token:

| Token         | Value     | Applies to                |
|---------------|-----------|---------------------------|
| `track.epic`  | `-0.04em` | `type.epic`               |
| `track.display`| `-0.03em`| `type.display`            |
| `track.headline`| `-0.02em`| `type.headline`, `title`  |
| `track.body`  | `-0.005em`| `type.lede`, `body`       |
| `track.label` | `0.04em`  | sans labels, eyebrows, micro |
| `track.caps`  | `0.12em`  | the **only** allowed all-caps usage (eyebrows, frame markers) |

### Constraints
- Body copy is **never tracked positive** except labels.
- Display type (`epic`, `display`) is **always negative-tracked** to compress optical mass.
- All-caps allowed **only** at sizes ≤ 13px with `track.caps`.

---

## 5. Leading (Line-Height)

| Token          | Value | Use                                        |
|----------------|------:|--------------------------------------------|
| `lead.tight`   | 0.92  | `type.epic`                                 |
| `lead.display` | 0.98  | `type.display`                              |
| `lead.headline`| 1.08  | `type.headline`, `type.title`               |
| `lead.body`    | 1.55  | `type.lede`, `type.body`                    |
| `lead.caption` | 1.40  | `type.caption`, `type.micro`                |

- Display leading **must** be sub-1 to create stacked-block density.
- Body leading **must** be ≥ 1.5 for editorial readability.
- Never `line-height: 1` (collides descenders) or `line-height: normal` (browser-dependent).

---

## 6. Hierarchy & Composition

### 6.1 Pairings
- Default pairing: **Serif display + Sans body**.
- Inverse pairing (sans display + serif body): allowed only in **Human Layer** chapter for tonal contrast.
- Mono: only as eyebrow/metadata; never as body or display.

### 6.2 Editorial Block Structure
A canonical editorial block has up to four parts, in this order:

1. **Eyebrow** — sans, `type.micro`, `track.caps`, all-caps. Optional. Acts as section marker (e.g., `001 — CHAPTER`).
2. **Display title** — serif, `type.epic` or `type.display`. Required.
3. **Lede** — sans or serif, `type.lede`. Optional, max 2 sentences.
4. **Body** — sans, `type.body`. Optional.

### 6.3 Vertical Spacing (within a block)
- Eyebrow → Title: **24–32px** (token `space.beat`).
- Title → Lede: **40–56px** (token `space.measure`).
- Lede → Body: **24px** (token `space.beat`).
- Block → Block (within scene): **120–200px** (token `space.scene`).

### 6.4 Measure (Line Length)
- Body text: **52–68 characters per line**. Enforce via `max-width: 38ch` (sans) / `42ch` (serif).
- Lede: **40–52 characters per line**.
- Display: as wide as the composition demands; never wrap mid-word; allow purposeful line breaks via `<wbr>` or `\n` in MDX.

---

## 7. Oversized Typography Logic

The project's signature is **type-as-image**. Rules:

- Oversized type (`type.epic`) appears **at most once per chapter** — it is a punctuation mark, not a refrain.
- Always lock to a **single line** if possible. If wrapping, max 2 lines, with manual line breaks.
- Always **off-grid by intent** — bleed past the column gutter, or sit in a single weighted column.
- Always paired with **silence**: ≥ 50% of the viewport surrounding it is empty.
- Color: **never accent color**. Display type uses the chapter's primary text color only.
- Reveal: word-stagger or block-mask reveal (`clip-path: inset(0 100% 0 0) → inset(0 0 0 0)`) with `EASE.cinematic`, `DUR.cinematic`.

---

## 8. Numerals & Special Characters

- Use **lining figures** in display, **oldstyle figures** in body (where the typeface supports both).
- Use **proportional figures** in prose, **tabular figures** in metadata/timecodes.
- Use **typographic apostrophes and quotes** (`'`, `"`, `"`, `"`) — never straight quotes.
- Use **em dashes (—)** for editorial breaks. Never `--`. Never spaced en dashes.
- Use **·** (interpunct, U+00B7) as the project's separator (e.g., `2025 · Chapter 03 · Drift`).

Configure via:
```css
font-feature-settings: "kern", "liga", "calt", "ss01";
font-variant-numeric: lining-nums proportional-nums;
```
Override per-context for tabular metadata.

---

## 9. Implementation Standards

### Tokens
- All type tokens live in `styles/tokens/typography.ts`. Tailwind v4 `@theme` exposes them as utilities.
- Never write raw `text-[40px]` Tailwind arbitrary values. Always use semantic tokens (`text-display`, `text-lede`, etc.).

### Components
- A single `<Type>` primitive in `components/primitives/Type.tsx` exposes `as`, `variant`, `tone`, `track`, `lead` props.
- All headings (`h1`–`h6`) consumed via `<Type>` or specialized `<DisplayTitle>`, `<EditorialBlock>` components.
- Raw `<h1>` in JSX is forbidden.

### Loading
- Critical fonts: `display: "block"` for ≤ 100ms swap window, then `display: "swap"`.
- Use `next/font` `preload: true` on the primary serif and primary sans only. Other weights load lazily.
- Avoid `font-synthesis: weight`. Set `font-synthesis: none`.

---

## 10. DO / DON'T

### DO
- DO let oversized type breathe with massive negative space.
- DO break layout grids with display titles intentionally.
- DO use serif italics for the title of a work or rare emphasis.
- DO control line breaks manually for display copy (`<br />` or `\n` in MDX).

### DON'T
- DON'T use more than 2 typefaces simultaneously.
- DON'T set body type below 16px.
- DON'T use `font-weight: 700+` for any weight in the project.
- DON'T center body paragraphs.
- DON'T justify text. Always left-aligned, ragged-right.
- DON'T use text-shadows or strokes on display type.
- DON'T animate font-weight or font-stretch transitions (unless variable axis with intent).

---

## 11. Cinematic Rationale

- Restraint in weight (≤ 500) is the difference between **editorial** and **promotional**.
- Negative tracking on display type compresses mass; this is what makes it feel "carved", not "typed".
- Tight leading on display + generous leading on body creates **rhythmic contrast** — the page breathes.
- Two typefaces feels intentional. Three feels like a moodboard. Four feels like Squarespace.
